<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 21 at 9:56PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>..Isolated pockets of freezing drizzle and freezing rain possible
through early Wednesday morning...
Light rain will overspread the Lower Hudson Valley around midnight
and continue into Wednesday morning. Surface temperatures across
parts of Orange and Putnam counties are subfreezing, in the mid
and upper 20s, allowing for some light freezing rain/drizzle at
the onset of the precipitation. A changeover to all rain is
expected overnight as temperatures slowly rise by early Wednesday
morning.
A trace or light glaze of ice may result in icy spots, especially
on any untreated travel surfaces.</description>
